<h1 class="lower">Create a new PERCEPTION MAP</h1>
<div style="width:400px;float:left;margin-top:100px;">
<% form_for :groupables, @groupable,
:url =>{:controller => 'groupables', :action => 'create' } do |f| -%>

  <p><strong>Perception maps</strong> are a way to present a user-friendly list which your participants can use to group their preferences
  using a simple drag-and-drop interface.</p>

  <p>To get started, give your perception map a title.  This is for your reference only, so give it a title that will help you
  remember the subject or content of this group (eg. "Quantity vs. quality perception map").</p>

<p><%= label_tag 'title:' %><br/>
<%= f.text_field :title %>
<%= f.hidden_field :project_id, :value => params[:id] %>
</p>


<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<%= link_to "Cancel", :controller => "project", :action => "edit", :id => params[:id] %>&nbsp;&nbsp;<%= submit_tag 'Next -->' %></p>

<% end -%>
</div>